22. Use Stack Widget in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Stack widget in Flutter is used to place widgets on top of each other (overlapping).

Similar to layers (like Photoshop)
Children are placed in order (first = bottom, last = top)
Use Positioned widget to control exact placement

//main code

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: StackExample(),
    );
  }
}

class StackExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Stack Widget Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Stack(
          children: [
            Container(
              height: 200,
              width: 200,
              color: Colors.blue,
            ),
            Positioned(
              top: 50,
              left: 50,
              child: Container(
                height: 100,
                width: 100,
                color: Colors.red,
              ),
            ),
            Positioned(
              bottom: 10,
              right: 10,
              child: Text(
                "Stack",
                style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 20),
              ),
            ),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}